Title: The Street Met the CALLING By Baby-Tudor-Kennedy aka Nico Racquel Almanza Subject:Lou Reed (Lou Lou Bear)
The street met the calling,
untamed,
forgotten sleep
, wrestling ecstasy into the night,
oblivious pounding,
devouring breath,
form against form,
and we are animals,
un-caged, without master,
without keeper,
or quieter,
or sin, without worship of anything other then GODS own heaven lust, created in your skin, moving. We strange beasts of Creation, are here, this is OUR machine, this city, and she is OUR FELINE, our instinctive impulse, and we will ravage the dawn, that dares to tame her, our muse, our rise to sun and glory, our passionate earthly tremor, our universal freedom birthed by one hour of climax.
